cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper is about improving the performance of Query Auto-Completion (QAC) in eCommerce search, which is a subfield of Information Retrieval. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper uses fastText embeddings to represent queries and candidate completions. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a ranking model that combines different features to learn to rank the candidate completions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as QAC is a common feature in many AI applications, and the paper proposes a personalized approach to improve its performance. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also possible as the paper applies the proposed method to a large eCommerce search engine and evaluates its performance using offline metrics.
